","bgcolor":"#353"},{"id":19,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-1120,660],"size":[780,280],"flags":{},"order":20,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"MarkdownNote"},"widgets_values":["# Qwen BF16 sprite workflow v2 - aggressive style conversion\n\nThis version is stronger because your latest result still looked very close to the original.\n\nChanges vs previous BF16 workflow:\n- Prompt now explicitly says to replace old cartoon rendering, linework, eye style, face style, hair rendering, and clothing shading.\n- LoRA strength = 1.15.\n- Steps = 36.\n- CFG = 4.5.\n- Denoise = 0.68.\n\nUse this to prove the BF16 model can strongly change style. After it works, back off settings:\n- Too much redesign: denoise 0.52-0.60 and LoRA 0.80-1.00.\n- Too little style: denoise 0.70-0.78 and LoRA 1.20.\n- Output too flat/cel-shaded: LoRA 0.60-0.85 and keep denoise around 0.60.\n\nThis unrolled workflow does not use the official one-node turbo subgraph. If you use the official subgraph instead, disable turbo mode for quality/style tests."],"title":"Instructions / BF16 aggressive tuning notes","color":"#222","bgcolor":"#000"},{"id":20,"type":"SaveImage","pos":[1190,-210],"size":[320,110],"flags":{},"order":18,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"images","type":"IMAGE","link":27}],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"SaveImage","cnr_id":"comfy-core","ver":"0.5.1"},"widgets_values":["style_out/qwen_bf16_sprite_lora_v2_aggressive"],"title":"OUTPUT - core Save Image (BF16 v2 aggressive)","color":"#232","bgcolor":"#353"},{"id":21,"type":"LoraLoaderModelOnly","pos":[520,-160],"size":[320,82],"flags":{},"order":10,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"model","type":"MODEL","link":30}],"outputs":[{"name":"MODEL","type":"MODEL","links":[31]}],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"LoraLoaderModelOnly"},"widgets_values":["Qwen-Image-Edit-2511-Anime-2000.safetensors",1.15],"title":"Anime LoRA - Qwen 2511 AGGRESSIVE","color":"#223","bgcolor":"#335"}],"links":[[1,1,0,3,0,"IMAGE"],